# /weekly-report — Generate HTML Progress Report

Aggregate work log entries and git data into a styled HTML progress report.

## Configuration
- **Project root:** `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}`
- **Work log path:** `{{WORK_LOG_PATH}}`
- **Reports output dir:** `{{REPORTS_OUTPUT_DIR}}`
- **Project name:** `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`
- **Git remote:** `{{GIT_REMOTE}}`
- **Task tracker:** `{{TASK_TRACKER_PATH}}`

## Steps

### Step 1 — Read Work Log Entries
Read `{{WORK_LOG_PATH}}`.
Identify entries from the current week (Monday to now) or since the last weekly report.
Parse each entry for: date, summary, deliverables, files changed, metrics, commits.
If no work log entries exist for the period, use git data alone.

### Step 2 — Get Git Commit Data
Run from `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}`:
```bash
git log --oneline --since="1 week ago" --format="%h|%s|%an|%ad" --date=short
```
Also run:
```bash
git diff --stat HEAD@{1.week.ago}..HEAD
```
Parse: commit count, unique authors, files changed, lines added/removed.

### Step 3 — Aggregate Metrics
Calculate totals for the reporting period:
- Total commits
- Total files changed (unique)
- Total lines added / removed
- Sessions logged
- Deliverables completed (from work log)
- Tasks completed (from `{{TASK_TRACKER_PATH}}` if available)

### Step 4 — Determine Milestones
From work log entries and task tracker, identify:
- Major features completed this week
- Features in progress (started but not finished)
- Blockers encountered and their resolution status
- Upcoming milestones for next week

### Step 5 — Generate HTML Report
Create an HTML file at `{{REPORTS_OUTPUT_DIR}}/week-[YYYY-WW].html` with:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>{{PROJECT_NAME}} — Weekly Report [date range]</title>
  <style>
    /* Clean, professional styling */
    /* Use system fonts, subtle colors, good spacing */
    /* Include print-friendly styles */
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Banner: project name, date range, report number -->
  <header>...</header>

  <!-- Navigation tabs if report is long -->
  <nav>
    <a href="#summary">Summary</a>
    <a href="#metrics">Metrics</a>
    <a href="#accomplishments">Accomplishments</a>
    <a href="#commits">Commits</a>
    <a href="#next-week">Next Week</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- Executive Summary: 3-5 bullet points of key highlights -->
  <section id="summary">
    <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>[Key highlight 1]</li>
      <li>[Key highlight 2]</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Metrics Dashboard: visual cards with numbers -->
  <section id="metrics">
    <h2>Metrics</h2>
    <div class="metrics-grid">
      <div class="metric-card">
        <span class="metric-value">N</span>
        <span class="metric-label">Commits</span>
      </div>
      <!-- More cards: files changed, lines added, tests passing, tasks done -->
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Accomplishments: grouped by area -->
  <section id="accomplishments">
    <h2>Accomplishments</h2>
    <!-- Group by: Backend, Frontend, Infrastructure, Docs -->
  </section>

  <!-- Commit Log: collapsible table -->
  <section id="commits">
    <h2>Commit Log</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Hash</th><th>Message</th><th>Author</th><th>Date</th></tr>
      <!-- One row per commit -->
    </table>
  </section>

  <!-- Milestones: progress bar or checklist -->
  <section id="milestones">
    <h2>Milestones</h2>
    <!-- Visual progress indicators -->
  </section>

  <!-- Next Week: planned work -->
  <section id="next-week">
    <h2>Next Week</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>[Planned item 1]</li>
      <li>[Planned item 2]</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <footer>
    Generated on [timestamp] by /weekly-report
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

### Step 6 — Update Work Log Header
Update the header of `{{WORK_LOG_PATH}}` with:
- Last report date
- Last report file path
- Running totals (total commits, total sessions)

### Step 7 — Report
Confirm: "Weekly report generated: [file path]"
Print a brief text summary of the key metrics.

## Notes
- Reports are cumulative for the week, not just one session
- If git history is shallow or unavailable, rely on work log entries only
- Keep the HTML self-contained (inline CSS, no external dependencies)
- Include a print stylesheet so the report looks good when printed to PDF
- Date range: Monday through the current day
- File naming: `week-2026-07.html` for week 7 of 2026
